  "prompt": "What is the success ratio to get B1/B2 visa?",
  "response": "The success ratio for B1/B2 visa (tourist/business visitor) applications varies depending on several factors, such as:\n\n1. Country of origin\n2. Individual applicant's profile\n3. Purpose of travel\n4. Financial stability\n5. Ties to home country\n6. Previous travel history\n\nGenerally speaking:\n- Overall approval rates range between 60-80%\n- Some countries have higher success rates than others\n- Most common rejection reasons include:\n  - Insufficient financial proof\n  - Weak ties to home country\n  - Incomplete documentation\n  - Previous immigration violations\n\nFactors that improve approval chances:\n- Strong financial background\n- Stable employment\n- Clear travel purpose\n- Previous international travel history\n- Strong family/professional ties in home country\n- Complete and accurate documentation\n\nSpecific success rates by country can vary, so it's recommended to:\n- Consult the nearest U.S. Embassy\n- Prepare comprehensive documentation\n- Be honest during the interview\n- Demonstrate strong intent to return\n\nWhile exact percentages change yearly, maintaining a strong application profile significantly improves visa approval probability.\n\nConsulting an immigration lawyer or experienced visa consultant can provide more personalized guidance.",
